of his playing 7.Nd2 belonged to his coach Arshak Petrosian who used this
system long ago. I couldn't recollect this opening occurred at the World
Championship Matches after Botvinnik-Tal. By the way, twenty years ago, the
then World Champion Anatoly Karpov invited me to assist him in preparing the
Modern Benoni against Garry Kasparov, but his young opponent didn't risk
playing it.} Bg7 8. e4 O-O 9. Be2 Na6 {Very often Black played immediately 9...
